com.niklasarndt.healthchecksio.model

Class Check

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.niklasarndt.healthchecksio.model.Check

  • public class Check
extends Object

    The model class Check represents a status check, identified by a UUID (write access) or unique key (read-only).

    For more information on the models, visit the wiki.

    Since:
    1.0.1

      • usesCronSchedule

        public boolean usesCronSchedule()

        A healthchecks.io check can either use a schedule in cron-format (schedule) or a fixed interval of seconds (timeout).

        Returns:
        Whether this check uses the cron schedule or a fixed interval.

      • isReadOnly

        public boolean isReadOnly()

        If you retrieve a check from healthchecks.io with a read-only key, you will receive an unique_key as well, which you can use to identify this check without actually knowing it's UUID.

        Returns:
        Whether this check was retrieved from with a read-only API key.

      • getUuid

        public String getUuid()

        Uses the pingUrl of the check (only available with write access!) to obtain the UUID.

        Returns:
        The UUID of the check (or null if read-only).

      • getUuidOrUniqueKey

        public String getUuidOrUniqueKey()
